  <data name="HowItWorksBody" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delimiter&lt;/strong&gt; — The character used to separate fields. German/European CSVs typically use &lt;code&gt;;&lt;/code&gt; while English CSVs use &lt;code&gt;,&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decimal separator&lt;/strong&gt; — The character used for decimal points. German: &lt;code&gt;1.234,56&lt;/code&gt; → English: &lt;code&gt;1,234.56&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thousands separator&lt;/strong&gt; — Only enable this if your file contains formatted numbers with thousands separators.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quoted fields&lt;/strong&gt; — Fields wrapped in quotes are protected from delimiter/separator substitution.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;mb-0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Privacy&lt;/strong&gt; — Your files are processed server-side and stored temporarily. Use the &lt;em&gt;Delete My Files&lt;/em&gt; button to remove them immediately.&lt;/p&gt;</value>
